      "span_text": "Potential causes for frequent infringements of health-related regulations are poor knowledge of regulations, lack of inspections, lack of sanctions, successful concealment of regulatory violations, and the tacit permission of inspectors. The ADDO program was an attempt to reduce the problem of irrational dispensing of medicines by DLDB shops."
